div.row-fluid
  div.span12
    div.hero-unit(style='padding:15px')
      h2 Asterank is an economic and scientific catalog of over 500,000 asteroids in our solar system.

    div.welcome-blurb.well
      img(style='float:right;padding-left:10px;width:300px;height:auto', src='http://i.imgur.com/vvAjG.jpg')
      p With all the recent hype around asteroid mining, I wanted real numbers.  How realistic are the trillion dollar estimates?  What about the costs and overhead?

      p I've attempted to calculate or infer things like asteroid mass and composition.  I’ve collected data on their orbits from multiple scientific sources.  Using this information, I estimate the costs and rewards of commercially exploiting rocks in space.

      p There are three major factors in this evaluation:
        ol
          li <strong>Cost of Materials</strong> - Asteroids are full of valuable ore.
          li <strong>Cost of Operations</strong> - Getting to an asteroid and moving the raw material isn't easy.
          li <strong>Relative Savings</strong> - The biggest obstacle to the commercialization of space is getting things into orbit.  How much money do we save by mining in space instead of sending material up from Earth?

      p Remember, the data that we have on these objects is very sparse.  I make a ton of assumptions.  Don't start a space mission based on these rankings.

    div.well(style='text-align:center;')
      form.form-inline(style='margin:0')
        div.search-thing
          span Show top
          select#top_num(style='margin:0 5px 0').input-small
            option(value=100) 100
            option(value=1000) 1,000
            option(value=5000) 5,000
            option(value=10000) 10,000+
          span  asteroids sorted by
          select#top_sort(style='margin:0 5px 0').input-xlarge
            option(value='score', selected) most cost effective
            option(value='price') most valuable
            option(value='closeness') closest
          input#submit.btn.btn-large.btn-primary(type='submit', value='Go', style='width:175px;')

div#results.row-fluid(style='display:none;')
  div.span3
    div#instructions
      h3 Click on an object to view its details.
    div#details(style='display:none;')
      h1
      table.table.table-bordered.table-condensed
        thead
          tr
            th Data
            th Value
        tbody
  div#tbl-container.span9(style='height:400px;overflow:scroll;overflow-x:auto;')
    table#tbl.table.table-bordered.table-striped.table-condensed
      thead(style='background-color:#fff')
        tr
          th Name
          th Score
          th Value ($)
          th Cost from Earth ($)
          th Closeness
          th Type
          th Aphelion (AU)
          th Perhelion (AU)
          th MOID (AU)
          th &Delta;V (km/s)
          th pha
      tbody(style='cursor:pointer;')

div#legend.row-fluid(style='margin-left:15px;display:none;')
  div.span10
    span
      a(href='#', onClick="$('#legend-details').toggle();return false;") Explain column names
    div#legend-details(style='display:none;')
      ul
      li Value - the current value of the raw materials in this object.
      li Cost from Earth - the hypothetical cost of getting the valuable material in this object from Earth into space (at SpaceX's predicted rate per kg)
      li MOID (=EMOID=Earth Minimum Orbit Intersect Distance) - how close the object may come to Earth.
      li Aphelion - Greatest distance from sun.
      li Perhelion - Least distance from sun.
      li &Delta;v (for spacecraft rendezvous) - Change in velocity required to rendezvous with this asteroid.
      li PHA (Potentially Hazardous Object) - whether this object is classified by scientists as potentially hazard to Earth.
      li Type (Asteroid Spectral Type) - the spectral classification of this object, which lets us guess its composition.

